\section*{EXAMPLE 2.7}

Classify the equation as a conditional equation, an identity, or a contradiction and then state the solution:
$8+3(a-4)=0$.

\section*{Solution}

\begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
\hline & $8+3(a-4)=0$ \\
\hline Distribute. & $8+3 a-12=0$ \\
\hline Combine like terms. & $3 a-4=0$ \\
\hline Add 4 to both sides. & $3 a-4+4=0+4$ \\
\hline Simplify. & $3 a=4$ \\
\hline Divide. & $\frac{3 a}{3}=\frac{4}{3}$ \\
\hline Simplify. & $a=\frac{4}{3}$ \\
\hline The equation is true when $a=\frac{4}{3}$. & This is a conditional equation. \\
\hline & The solution is $a=\frac{4}{3}$. \\
\hline
\end{tabular}

