\hline Translate into an equation. & $m \quad=0.40 \quad \times \quad 750$ \\
\hline Solve the equation. & $m=300$ \\
\hline Write a complete sentence. & The mark-up on the painting was $\$ 300$. \\
\hline \multicolumn{2}{|l|}{(b)} \\
\hline Identify what you are asked to find, and choose a variable to represent it. & \begin{tabular}{l}
What is the list price? \\
Let $p=$ the list price.
\end{tabular} \\
\hline Write a sentence that gives the information to find it. & The list price is original cost plus the mark-up \\
\hline Translate into an equation. & $p \quad=750 \quad+\quad 300$ \\
\hline Solve the equation. & $p=1,050$ \\
\hline Check. & \begin{tabular}{l}
Is the list price more than the original cost? \\
Is $\$ 1,050$ more than $\$ 750$ ? Yes.
\end{tabular} \\
\hline Write a complete sentence. & The list price of the painting was \$1,050. \\
\hline
\end{tabular}

