Write the appropriate formula.
$$A=\frac{1}{2} b h$$

\begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
\hline Substitute in the given information. & $126=\frac{1}{2} \cdot 18 \cdot h$ \\
\hline Step 5. Solve the equation. & $126=9 h$ \\
\hline Divide both sides by 9 . & $14=h$ \\
\hline
\end{tabular}

\section*{Step 6. Check.}
$$\begin{aligned}
A & =\frac{1}{2} b h \\
126 & \stackrel{?}{=} \frac{1}{2} \cdot 18 \cdot 14 \\
126 & =126 \checkmark
\end{aligned}$$

